And, just like that,

1:09:44.786 --> 1:09:46.821
she gives me a room
in her house, this...

1:09:47.789 --> 1:09:48.923
gorgeous house.

1:09:50.457 --> 1:09:52.827
My sister and her husband,
Nick, they look like

1:09:53.360 --> 1:09:55.630
a jeans commercial
for the perfect family,

1:09:55.830 --> 1:09:58.365
complete with
their beautiful daughter.

1:09:59.366 --> 1:10:01.301
And it was going well.

1:10:02.036 --> 1:10:03.203
Really well.

1:10:04.839 --> 1:10:05.873
And then this one week,

1:10:06.107 --> 1:10:08.475
Heather goes out of town
for business.

1:10:08.676 --> 1:10:10.578
And... and Nick.

1:10:14.115 --> 1:10:15.315
Suddenly this...

1:10:16.617 --> 1:10:17.719
this shift.

1:10:18.986 --> 1:10:20.888
<i>He starts letting off steam.</i>

1:10:21.589 --> 1:10:25.459
<i>Heather's always right</i>
<i>and he's always wrong.</i>

1:10:26.194 --> 1:10:28.596
I get so pissed off at Heather

1:10:28.796 --> 1:10:30.998
who ended up
with this perfect life

1:10:31.199 --> 1:10:32.365
and I just think,

1:10:32.600 --> 1:10:35.536
why can't I just have that,
even just for a night?

1:10:36.336 --> 1:10:39.907
<i>And I lean into him.</i>

1:10:43.544 --> 1:10:46.581
<i>I wake up</i>
<i>with a hole in my stomach</i>

1:10:46.948 --> 1:10:48.348
and Nick is fine...

1:10:49.751 --> 1:10:51.018
like nothing happened.

1:10:53.955 --> 1:10:55.623
And that's when I see it.

1:10:57.058 --> 1:10:58.526
This darkness.

1:10:59.627 --> 1:11:00.795
Staring at me.

1:11:01.896 --> 1:11:03.564
It... It knows.

1:11:04.699 --> 1:11:06.567
